      "writtenOn": "2026-03-11T22:01:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What about union of { uword key_data + u32 key_index } (there is no problem with STATIC_ASSERT_SIZEOF because op-\u003euser_data can be u32 instead of uword) inside vnet_crypto_op_t.\nAs a result:\n1. There is no need to use additional parameter of key_data for these function type and key_data will be bind to op.\n2. Prepare SIMPLE \u0026 CHAINED key_data before data path.\n3. Prepare key_data for specific thread_index for more then one op object (for example esp_encrypt.c inside condition \u0027if (sa_index0 !\u003d current_sa_index)\u0027)\n4. Minimize processing inside vnet_crypto_process_ops_call_handler\n5. There is no need to get key object via op-\u003ekey_index for each op inside vnet_crypto_process_ops_call_handler.",
